for python3 (use pip3):
Install cv2
Install PyQt
Install imutils
Install progressbar

Make the app runnable
	-Navigate with the terminal in /home/pi/Desktop/Raspberry/Python
	-sudo chmod +x run.sh

Install LCD-Touchscreen drivers
	-sudo nano /boot/config.txt
	-Append the following lines at the bottom:
		#Uncomment to set LCD screen set up
		hdmi_group=2
		hdmi_mode=1
		hdmi_mode=87
		hdmi_cvt 800 480 60 6 0 0 0	
	-Navigate in the terminal to the Rasberry folder
	-Install the drivers with the following commands:
		tar xzvf joy-IT-lcd5-driver.tar.gz (if the LCD-show folder has not been decompressed yet)
		cd LCD-show/
		sudo bash ./LCD5-show
	-reboot with the LCD-Touchscreen plugged
  
Make the app runnable
	-cd /home/pi/Desktop/MeasureAngleFreqCVGui
	-sudo chmod +x run.sh
